This paper is about program synthesis, which is a subfield of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to improve the synthesis process, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the proposed technique in two different application domains, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of conflict-driven learning to improve the synthesis process, which is related to constraint programming (cs.CR).
